NAME
	topic_client_unsubscribe - unregister a process to stop receiving messages published in a topic.

SYNOPSIS
	#include <topic.h>

	int topic_client_unsubscribe(topicid_t id)

DESCRIPTION
	topic_client_unsubscribe() allows a process to remove itself from the subscriber list of a topic. If the specified topic doesn't exist, it returns an error.

RETURN VALUE
	On success, zero is returned. Otherwise, a value of -1 is returned, and the global variable errno is set to indicate the error.

ERRORS
	If the specified topic doesn't exist, ENOENT is returned.
	If the user wasn't registered in this topic, EINVAL is returned.
